Detailed Description

Advertising Campaign Model.

Represents an advertising campaign with budget settings, time frames, and relationship with banners. Campaign can be active or inactive.

See also
Banner

Activate the campaign.

Sets the is_active flag to True and saves the object to the database. Campaign starts showing ads after activation.

str Success message

42 def activate(self):
43 """!
44 @brief Activate the campaign
45

47 Campaign starts showing ads after activation.
48
49 @return str Success message

Get active banners with platform filtering.

Retrieves active banners with optional platform filtering.

Parameters
platformTarget platform: 'iOS', 'Android', or None for all
Returns
QuerySet of active Banner objects

Definition at line 19 of file services.py.

19 def get_active_banners(platform=None):
20 """!
21 @brief Get active banners with platform filtering
22
23 Retrieves active banners with optional platform filtering.
24
25 @param platform Target platform: 'iOS', 'Android', or None for all
26 @return QuerySet of active Banner objects
27 """
28 campaigns = Campaign.objects.filter(is_active=True)
29
30 if platform and platform in ['iOS', 'Android']:
31 campaigns = campaigns.filter(target_platform__in=[platform, 'Both'])
32
33 banners = Banner.objects.filter(campaign__in=campaigns)
34 return banners

Graph Legend

This page explains how to interpret the graphs that are generated by doxygen.

Consider the following example:

/*! Invisible class because of truncation */
class Invisible { };
/*! Truncated class, inheritance relation is hidden */
class Truncated : public Invisible { };
/* Class not documented with doxygen comments */
class Undocumented { };
/*! Class that is inherited using public inheritance */
class PublicBase : public Truncated { };
/*! A template class */
template<class T> class Templ { };
/*! Class that is inherited using protected inheritance */
class ProtectedBase { };
/*! Class that is inherited using private inheritance */
class PrivateBase { };
/*! Class that is used by the Inherited class */
class Used { };
/*! Super class that inherits a number of other classes */
class Inherited : public PublicBase,
protected ProtectedBase,
private PrivateBase,
public Undocumented,
public Templ<int>
{
private:
Used *m_usedClass;
};

This will result in the following graph:

The boxes in the above graph have the following meaning:

  • A filled gray box represents the struct or class for which the graph is generated.
  • A box with a black border denotes a documented struct or class.
  • A box with a gray border denotes an undocumented struct or class.
  • A box with a red border denotes a documented struct or class forwhich not all inheritance/containment relations are shown. A graph is truncated if it does not fit within the specified boundaries.

The arrows have the following meaning:

  • A blue arrow is used to visualize a public inheritance relation between two classes.
  • A dark green arrow is used for protected inheritance.
  • A dark red arrow is used for private inheritance.
  • A purple dashed arrow is used if a class is contained or used by another class. The arrow is labelled with the variable(s) through which the pointed class or struct is accessible.
  • A yellow dashed arrow denotes a relation between a template instance and the template class it was instantiated from. The arrow is labelled with the template parameters of the instance.
  • Generated by 1.9.8

127 def save(self, *args, **kwargs):
128 # –ê–≤—Ç–æ–º–∞—Ç–∏—á–µ—Å–∫–æ–µ –æ–ø—Ä–µ–¥–µ–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ç–∏–ø–∞ –º–µ–¥–∏–∞
129 if self.media_file:
130 extension = self.media_file.name.split('.')[-1].lower()
131 if extension in ['png', 'jpg', 'jpeg', 'gif']:
132 self.media_type = 'image'
133 elif extension in ['mp4', 'avi', 'mov']:
134 self.media_type = 'video'
135 super().save(*args, **kwargs)

172 """CTR (Click-Through Rate) –≤ –ø—Ä–æ—Ü–µ–Ω—Ç–∞—Ö"""

1"""
2@package bannerflow_app.models
3@brief Data models for BannerFlow Manager system
4
5This module contains Django models for managing advertising campaigns and banners.
6"""
7
8from django.db import models
9
10class Campaign(models.Model):
11 """!
12 @brief Advertising Campaign Model
13
14 Represents an advertising campaign with budget settings, time frames,
15 and relationship with banners. Campaign can be active or inactive.
16
17 @see Banner
18 """
19
20 name = models.CharField(max_length=255)
21 """!< Campaign name (required field)"""
22
23 budget = models.DecimalField(max_digits=10, decimal_places=2)
24 """!< Campaign budget in rubles"""
25
26 is_active = models.BooleanField(default=False)
27 """!< Campaign activity flag (True - active, False - inactive)"""
28
29 start_date = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)
30 """!< Campaign start date and time"""
31
32 end_date = models.DateTimeField(null=True, blank=True)
33 """!< Campaign end date and time"""
34
35 target_platform = models.CharField(
36 max_length=10,
37 choices=[('iOS', 'iOS'), ('Android', 'Android'), ('Both', 'Both')],
38 default='Both'
39 )
40 """!< Target platform for ad display"""
41
42 def activate(self):
43 """!
44 @brief Activate the campaign
45
46 Sets the is_active flag to True and saves the object to the database.
47 Campaign starts showing ads after activation.
48
49 @return str Success message
50 """
51 self.is_active = True
52 self.save()
53 return f"Campaign '{self.name}' activated"
54
55 def deactivate(self):
56 """!
57 @brief Deactivate the campaign
58
59 Sets the is_active flag to False and saves the object to the database.
60 Campaign stops showing ads after deactivation.
61
62 @return str Success message
63 """
64 self.is_active = False
65 self.save()
66 return f"Campaign '{self.name}' deactivated"
67
68 def __str__(self):
69 """!
70 @brief String representation of campaign
71
72 @return str Campaign name and status
73 """
74 status = "Active" if self.is_active else "Inactive"
75 return f"{self.name} ({status})"
76
77class Banner(models.Model):
78 """!
79 @brief Advertising Banner Model
80
81 Represents an advertising banner linked to a campaign.
82 Contains media content and display settings.
83 """
84
85 campaign = models.ForeignKey(Campaign, on_delete=models.CASCADE)
86 """!< Reference to parent campaign (foreign key)"""
87
88 title = models.CharField(max_length=255)
89 """!< Banner title"""
90
91 image_url = models.URLField()
92 """!< URL of banner image or video"""
93
94 is_active = models.BooleanField(default=True)
95 """!< Banner activity flag"""
96
97 created_at = models.DateTimeField(auto_now_add=True)
98 """!< Banner creation date and time"""
99
100 def __str__(self):
101 """!
102 @brief String representation of banner
103
104 @return str Banner title
105 """
106 return f"Banner: {self.title}"

121def api_banners(request):
122 """API –¥–ª—è –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –±–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä–æ–≤"""
123 try:
124 from .models import Campaign
125 campaigns = Campaign.objects.filter(status='active')
126
127 banners_data = []

129 for banner in campaign.banners.all():

131 'id': banner.id,
132 'title': banner.title,
133 'campaign': campaign.name,
134 'status': campaign.status,
135 })

37def generate_banner(request):

1"""
2@package bannerflow_app.services
3@brief Service layer for BannerFlow Manager business logic
4
5This module contains service classes for business operations.
6"""
7
8from django.core.mail import send_mail
9from .models import Campaign, Banner
10
11class BannerService:
12 """!
13 @brief Service for banner-related operations
14
15 Provides business logic for banner management and operations.
16 """
17
18 @staticmethod
19 def get_active_banners(platform=None):
20 """!
21 @brief Get active banners with platform filtering
22
23 Retrieves active banners with optional platform filtering.
24
25 @param platform Target platform: 'iOS', 'Android', or None for all
26 @return QuerySet of active Banner objects
27 """
28 campaigns = Campaign.objects.filter(is_active=True)
29
30 if platform and platform in ['iOS', 'Android']:
31 campaigns = campaigns.filter(target_platform__in=[platform, 'Both'])
32
33 banners = Banner.objects.filter(campaign__in=campaigns)
34 return banners
35
36 @staticmethod
37 def check_budget_and_notify(campaign):
38 """!
39 @brief Check campaign budget and send notifications
40
41 Verifies if campaign budget is exhausted and sends email notifications.
42
43 @param campaign Campaign object to check
44 @return bool True if budget is exceeded, False otherwise
45 """
46 # Placeholder implementation
47 budget_exceeded = False
48
49 if budget_exceeded:
50 send_mail(
51 'Campaign Budget Exceeded',
52 f'Campaign "{campaign.name}" has exceeded its budget.',
53 'noreply@bannerflow.com',
54 ['marketer@company.com'],
55 fail_silently=False,
56 )
57
58 return budget_exceeded

31 return render(request, 'bannerflow_app/banner_generator.html', {
32 'templates': [],
33 'game_data': [],
34 'error': str(e)

37def generate_banner(request):
38 """–ì–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏—è –±–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä–∞"""
39 from django.contrib import messages
40 from django.shortcuts import redirect
41
42 if request.method == 'POST':
43 try:
44 from .models import BannerTemplate, GameData, GeneratedBanner
45 from .banner_generator import BannerGenerator
46 import tempfile
47 import os
48 from django.core.files import File
49
50 template_id = request.POST.get('template')
51 game_data_id = request.POST.get('game_data')
52 banner_name = request.POST.get('name', '–ù–æ–≤—ã–π –±–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä')
53
54 template = BannerTemplate.objects.get(id=template_id)
55 game_data = GameData.objects.get(id=game_data_id)
56
57 # –ì–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∏—Ä—É–µ–º HTML
58 html_content = BannerGenerator.generate_html(template, game_data)
59
60 # –°–æ–∑–¥–∞—ë–º —ç–∫—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç –¥–ª—è Godot
61 godot_script = BannerGenerator.export_for_godot(
62 html_content,
63 banner_name,
64 template
65 )
66
67 # –°–æ—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—è–µ–º –≤ –±–∞–∑–µ
68 banner = GeneratedBanner.objects.create(
69 name=banner_name,
70 template=template,
71 game_data=game_data,
72 html_content=html_content,
73 )
74
75 # –°–æ—Ö—Ä–∞–Ω—è–µ–º —Ñ–∞–π–ª —ç–∫—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç–∞
76 with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(mode='w', suffix='.gd', delete=False, encoding='utf-8') as f:
77 f.write(godot_script)
78 temp_path = f.name
79
80 with open(temp_path, 'rb') as f:
81 banner.godot_export.save(f'banner_{banner.id}.gd', File(f))
82
83 os.unlink(temp_path)
84
85 messages.success(request, f'–ë–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä "{banner_name}" —É—Å–ø–µ—à–Ω–æ —Å–æ–∑–¥–∞–Ω!')
86 return redirect('banner_preview', banner_id=banner.id)
87
88 except Exception as e:
89 messages.error(request, f'–û—à–∏–±–∫–∞ –≥–µ–Ω–µ—Ä–∞—Ü–∏–∏: {str(e)}')
90 return redirect('banner_generator')
91
92 return redirect('banner_generator')
93
94

107 def cleanup():
108 try:
109 os.unlink(temp_path)
110 except:
111 pass
112
113 # –ü—Ä–∏–∫—Ä–µ–ø–ª—è–µ–º cleanup –∫ response
114 response._resource_to_cleanup = temp_path
115
116 return response
117
118 except Exception as e:

121def api_banners(request):
122 """API –¥–ª—è –ø–æ–ª—É—á–µ–Ω–∏—è –±–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä–æ–≤"""
123 try:
124 from .models import Campaign
125 campaigns = Campaign.objects.filter(status='active')
126
127 banners_data = []
128 for campaign in campaigns:
129 for banner in campaign.banners.all():
130 banners_data.append({
131 'id': banner.id,
132 'title': banner.title,
133 'campaign': campaign.name,
134 'status': campaign.status,
135 })
136
137 return JsonResponse({'banners': banners_data})
138 except Exception as e:
139 return JsonResponse({'error': str(e)}, status=500)

145def export_banner(request, banner_id):
146 """–≠–∫—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç –±–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä–∞ –¥–ª—è Godot - –†–ê–ë–û–ß–ê–Ø –í–ï–†–°–ò–Ø"""
147 try:
148 from .models import GeneratedBanner
149 from .banner_generator import BannerGenerator
150 from django.http import FileResponse
151 import tempfile
152 import os
153
154 banner = GeneratedBanner.objects.get(id=banner_id)
155
156 # –°–æ–∑–¥–∞–µ–º —ç–∫—Å–ø–æ—Ä—Ç –¥–ª—è Godot
157 godot_script = BannerGenerator.export_for_godot(
158 banner.html_content,
159 banner.name,
160 banner.template
161 )
162
163 # –°–æ–∑–¥–∞–µ–º –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–π —Ñ–∞–π–ª —Å —Ä–∞—Å—à–∏—Ä–µ–Ω–∏–µ–º .gd
164 with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile(
165 mode='w',
166 suffix='.gd',
167 delete=False,
168 encoding='utf-8'
169 ) as temp_file:
170 temp_file.write(godot_script)
171 temp_path = temp_file.name
172
173 # –°–æ–∑–¥–∞–µ–º –∏–º—è —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞
174 filename = f"banner_{banner.id}.gd"
175
176 # –û—Ç–ø—Ä–∞–≤–ª—è–µ–º —Ñ–∞–π–ª –¥–ª—è —Å–∫–∞—á–∏–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è
177 response = FileResponse(
178 open(temp_path, 'rb'),
179 as_attachment=True,
180 filename=filename,
181 content_type='text/plain'
182 )
183
184 # –£–¥–∞–ª—è–µ–º –≤—Ä–µ–º–µ–Ω–Ω—ã–π —Ñ–∞–π–ª
185 import atexit
186 def cleanup():
187 try:
188 os.unlink(temp_path)
189 except:
190 pass
191 atexit.register(cleanup)
192
193 return response
194
195 except GeneratedBanner.DoesNotExist:
196 from django.http import HttpResponse
197 return HttpResponse("–ë–∞–Ω–Ω–µ—Ä –Ω–µ –Ω–∞–π–¥–µ–Ω", status=404)
198 except Exception as e:
199 from django.http import HttpResponse
200 return HttpResponse(f'–û—à–∏–±–∫–∞: {str(e)}', status=500)
